        {
            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20scripture%2C%20Paul%20reveals%20the%20connection%20between%20your%20mouth%20and%20your%20heart%20in%20the%20expression%20of%20your%20faith.%20Jesus%20said%2C%20%22For%20whatever%20is%20in%20your%20heart%20determines%20what%20you%20say%22%20(Matthew%2012%3A34).%20Clearly%2C%20Jesus%20is%20the%20Word%20(John%201%3A1)%3B%20therefore%2C%20when%20you%20speak%20the%20Word%2C%20you%20are%20speaking%20Jesus%20into%20your%20situation.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFaith%20begins%20in%20the%20heart%2C%20a%20heart%20that%20is%20fully%20persuaded%20that%20the%20promises%20of%20God%20are%20true.%20Once%20such%20faith%20is%20deep%20within%20your%20heart%2C%20your%20mouth%20will%20begin%20to%20reflect%20that%20faith%20by%20the%20words%20you%20say.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhatever%20you%20believe%20in%20your%20heart%20about%20Jesus%2C%20you%20confess%20with%20your%20mouth.%20You%20believe%20that%20God%20raised%20Jesus%20from%20the%20dead%2C%20and%20you%20confess%2C%20%22Jesus%20is%20Lord.%22%20You%20believe%20that%20Jesus%20paid%20for%20your%20healing%2C%20and%20you%20confess%2C%20%22Jesus%20is%20my%20Healer.%22%20You%20believe%20that%20Jesus%20is%20your%20Provider%2C%20and%20you%20confess%2C%20%22Jesus%20is%20my%20Shepherd.%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIf%20you%20call%20upon%20the%20name%20of%20the%20Lord%20in%20faith%2C%20you%20will%20receive%20that%20promise%20for%20salvation%2C%20blessing%2C%20healing%2C%20or%20deliverance.%20After%20you%20receive%20the%20promise%2C%20speak%20the%20Word%20and%20watch%20Jesus%20show%20up%20on%20the%20scene!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Chr.17:1-18:34",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Chronicles%2017%3A1-18%3A34%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJehoshaphat%20Rules%20in%20Judah%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Jehoshaphat%2C%20Asa%26%23x2019%3Bs%20son%2C%20became%20the%20next%20king.%20He%20strengthened%20Judah%20to%20stand%20against%20any%20attack%20from%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20stationed%20troops%20in%20all%20the%20fortified%20towns%20of%20Judah%2C%20and%20he%20assigned%20additional%20garrisons%20to%20the%20land%20of%20Judah%20and%20to%20the%20towns%20of%20Ephraim%20that%20his%20father%2C%20Asa%2C%20had%20captured.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20with%20Jehoshaphat%20because%20he%20followed%20the%20example%20of%20his%20father%26%23x2019%3Bs%20early%20years%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E17%3A3%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Some%20Hebrew%20manuscripts%20read%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20example%20of%20his%20father%2C%20David.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20did%20not%20worship%20the%20images%20of%20Baal.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20sought%20his%20father%26%23x2019%3Bs%20God%20and%20obeyed%20his%20commands%20instead%20of%20following%20the%20evil%20practices%20of%20the%20kingdom%20of%20Israel.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20established%20Jehoshaphat%26%23x2019%3Bs%20control%20over%20the%20kingdom%20of%20Judah.%20All%20the%20people%20of%20Judah%20brought%20gifts%20to%20Jehoshaphat%2C%20so%20he%20became%20very%20wealthy%20and%20highly%20esteemed.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20was%20deeply%20committed%20to%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E17%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EHis%20heart%20was%20courageous%20in.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20ways%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20He%20removed%20the%20pagan%20shrines%20and%20Asherah%20poles%20from%20Judah.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20the%20third%20year%20of%20his%20reign%20Jehoshaphat%20sent%20his%20officials%20to%20teach%20in%20all%20the%20towns%20of%20Judah.%20These%20officials%20included%20Ben-hail%2C%20Obadiah%2C%20Zechariah%2C%20Nethanel%2C%20and%20Micaiah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20sent%20Levites%20along%20with%20them%2C%20including%20Shemaiah%2C%20Nethaniah%2C%20Zebadiah%2C%20Asahel%2C%20Shemiramoth%2C%20Jehonathan%2C%20Adonijah%2C%20Tobijah%2C%20and%20Tob-adonijah.%20He%20also%20sent%20out%20the%20priests%20Elishama%20and%20Jehoram.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20took%20copies%20of%20the%20Book%20of%20the%20Law%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20traveled%20around%20through%20all%20the%20towns%20of%20Judah%2C%20teaching%20the%20people.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20fear%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20fell%20over%20all%20the%20surrounding%20kingdoms%20so%20that%20none%20of%20them%20wanted%20to%20declare%20war%20on%20Jehoshaphat.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3ESome%20of%20the%20Philistines%20brought%20him%20gifts%20and%20silver%20as%20tribute%2C%20and%20the%20Arabs%20brought%207%2C700%20rams%20and%207%2C700%20male%20goats.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Jehoshaphat%20became%20more%20and%20more%20powerful%20and%20built%20fortresses%20and%20storage%20cities%20throughout%20Judah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_13%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20stored%20numerous%20supplies%20in%20Judah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20towns%20and%20stationed%20an%20army%20of%20seasoned%20troops%20at%20Jerusalem.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_14%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EHis%20army%20was%20enrolled%20according%20to%20ancestral%20clans.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging-sp%22%3EFrom%20Judah%20there%20were%20300%2C000%20troops%20organized%20in%20units%20of%201%2C000%2C%20under%20the%20command%20of%20Adnah.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_15%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3ENext%20in%20command%20was%20Jehohanan%2C%20who%20commanded%20280%2C000%20troops.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_16%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3ENext%20was%20Amasiah%20son%20of%20Zicri%2C%20who%20volunteered%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20service%2C%20with%20200%2C000%20troops%20under%20his%20command.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_17%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22ext-hanging%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20Benjamin%20there%20were%20200%2C000%20troops%20equipped%20with%20bows%20and%20shields.%20They%20were%20under%20the%20command%20of%20Eliada%2C%20a%20veteran%20soldier.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_18%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3ENext%20in%20command%20was%20Jehozabad%2C%20who%20commanded%20180%2C000%20armed%20men.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_17_19%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2217%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-fl-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20were%20the%20troops%20stationed%20in%20Jerusalem%20to%20serve%20the%20king%2C%20besides%20those%20Jehoshaphat%20stationed%20in%20the%20fortified%20towns%20throughout%20Judah.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_18_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJehoshaphat%20and%20Ahab%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoshaphat%20enjoyed%20great%20riches%20and%20high%20esteem%2C%20and%20he%20made%20an%20alliance%20with%20Ahab%20of%20Israel%20by%20having%20his%20son%20marry%20Ahab%26%23x2019%3Bs%20daughter.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_18_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EA%20few%20years%20later%20he%20went%20to%20Samaria%20to%20visit%20Ahab%2C%20who%20prepared%20a%20great%20banquet%20for%20him%20and%20his%20officials.%20They%20butchered%20great%20numbers%20of%20sheep%2C%20goats%2C%20and%20cattle%20for%20the%20feast.%20Then%20Ahab%20enticed%20Jehoshaphat%20to%20join%20forces%20with%20him%20to%20recover%20Ramoth-gilead.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_18_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWill%20you%20go%20with%20me%20to%20Ramoth-gilead%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20King%20Ahab%20of%20Israel%20asked%20King%20Jehoshaphat%20of%20Judah.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EJehoshaphat%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhy%2C%20of%20course!%20You%20and%20I%20are%20as%20one%2C%20and%20my%20troops%20are%20your%20troops.%20We%20will%20certainly%20join%20you%20in%20battle.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_18_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Jehoshaphat%20added%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BBut%20first%20let%26%23x2019%3Bs%20find%20out%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_18_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20king%20of%20Israel%20summoned%20the%20prophets%2C%20400%26%23xA0%3Bof%20them%2C%20and%20asked%20them%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BShould%20we%20go%20to%20war%20against%20Ramoth-gilead%2C%20or%20should%20I%20hold%20back%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EThey%20all%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYes%2C%20go%20right%20ahead!%20God%20will%20give%20the%20king%20victory.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_18_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Jehoshaphat%20asked%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BIs%20there%20not%20also%20a%20prophet%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20here%3F%20We%20should%20ask%20him%20the%20same%20question.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_18_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20king%20of%20Israel%20replied%20to%20Jehoshaphat%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThere%20is%20one%20more%20man%20who%20could%20consult%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20for%20us%2C%20but%20I%20hate%20him.%20He%20never%20prophesies%20anything%20but%20trouble%20for%20me!%20His%20name%20is%20Micaiah%20son%20of%20Imlah.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EJehoshaphat%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThat%26%23x2019%3Bs%20not%20the%20way%20a%20king%20should%20talk!%20Let%26%23x2019%3Bs%20hear%20what%20he%20has%20to%20say.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_18_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2F